<section class="step settings-step">
  <div class="step-head">
    <h2>Settings</h2>
    <span id="settings-status" class="status"></span>
  </div>

  <form id="settings-form" class="settings-form">
    <div class="settings-row">
      <label for="model-select">Claude model</label>
      <div class="settings-control">
        <select id="model-select" name="model">
          <option value="">Use server default</option>
        </select>
        <div class="settings-hint" id="model-hint"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="settings-row">
      <label for="api-key-input">Your Anthropic API key</label>
      <div class="settings-control">
        <div class="api-key-state" id="api-key-state" data-state="loading">
          <span class="api-key-badge" id="api-key-badge">Loading…</span>
          <button type="button" class="api-key-remove" id="api-key-remove" hidden>Remove key</button>
        </div>
        <input id="api-key-input" name="apiKey" type="password" autocomplete="off" placeholder="sk-ant-…">
        <div class="settings-hint" id="api-key-hint">
          Stored encrypted at rest. Leave blank to keep the existing value.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="settings-actions">
      <button type="submit" class="primary" id="settings-save">Save</button>
    </div>
  </form>

  <section class="billing-section" id="billing" hidden>
    <h3>Tokens</h3>
    <p class="settings-hint">
      Buy a token pack to use a non-default Claude model without
      bringing your own API key. Tokens are consumed by Claude
      input + output tokens on each <em>Propose</em> or <em>Refine</em>.
      When the balance hits zero, requests revert to the server default
      model until you top up.
    </p>
    <div class="billing-balance" id="billing-balance">Loading…</div>
    <div class="billing-chart" id="billing-chart" hidden>
      <h4>Usage — last 30 days</h4>
      <svg id="billing-chart-svg" viewBox="0 0 600 100" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-label="Daily token usage"></svg>
      <div class="billing-chart-meta" id="billing-chart-meta"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="billing-packs" id="billing-packs"></div>
    <div class="billing-status" id="billing-status"></div>
  </section>

  <details class="settings-help">
    <summary>Learn how to create a secure API key</summary>
    <div class="settings-help-body">
      <p>
        Anthropic keys are scoped to a <strong>Workspace</strong>. Putting
        this app's key in its own workspace means a leaked or misused key
        can only spend that workspace's budget — it can't reach any of
        your other Anthropic projects.
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          Sign in to the
          <a href="https://console.anthropic.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Anthropic Console</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          Open <strong>Settings → Workspaces</strong> and click
          <strong>Create Workspace</strong>. Name it something specific
          like <em>Spreadsheet Transform</em> so you'll recognise it
          later.
        </li>
        <li>
          Open the new workspace and set a
          <strong>monthly spend limit</strong> under
          <strong>Settings → Limits</strong>. Pick the smallest amount
          that covers your expected use — this is your last line of
          defence if the key leaks.
        </li>
        <li>
          In the same workspace, go to
          <strong>API Keys → Create Key</strong>. Give the key a
          descriptive name (e.g. <em>sstransform-prod</em>) so you can
          revoke it without guessing.
        </li>
        <li>
          Copy the <code>sk-ant-…</code> value the console shows
          <em>once</em> and paste it into the field above. Click
          <strong>Save</strong>. The key is encrypted before it's
          written to disk; this app never displays it back to you.
        </li>
        <li>
          To revoke later, return to that workspace's
          <strong>API Keys</strong> page and delete the key — requests
          from this app will start failing on the next call. Use
          <strong>Remove key</strong> above to also drop the encrypted
          copy stored here.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </details>
</section>
